      <div>
        <h2>Why Professional Lighting Installation Matters</h2>
        <p>Lighting circuits carry real electrical loads, and improper installation creates fire risks, overloaded circuits, and code violations. Recessed lights installed in insulated ceilings require IC-rated housings to prevent heat buildup. Outdoor fixtures need weatherproof wiring and GFCI protection. Chandeliers over a certain weight demand reinforced junction boxes rated for the load.</p>
        <p>Osborne Electric handles these details so you get lighting that looks great and performs safely for years. Every installation meets current NEC and Utah electrical codes, and we pull permits when required.</p>
        <ul class="features-list">
          <li>Proper circuit load calculations for every project</li>
          <li>IC-rated housings for insulated ceiling installations</li>
          <li>Weatherproof connections for all outdoor lighting</li>
          <li>GFCI protection where code requires it</li>
          <li>Permits pulled and inspections coordinated</li>
        </ul>
