    </div>
    <div class="faq-list">
      <details class="faq-details">
        <summary>How much does recessed lighting installation cost in Utah?</summary>
        <div class="faq-details-body">
          <p>Recessed lighting installation in Utah typically costs $150 to $300 per light, depending on ceiling type, insulation, and whether new wiring is required. Most homeowners install 4 to 8 lights per room. Osborne Electric provides free estimates so you know the exact cost before work begins. Call <a href="tel:801-885-4521">801-885-4521</a> for a quote.</p>
        </div>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-details">
        <summary>Is it worth upgrading to LED lighting?</summary>
        <div class="faq-details-body">
          <p>LED lighting uses up to 75% less energy than incandescent bulbs and lasts 25 times longer. For a typical Utah home, switching to LED can save $100 to $200 per year on electricity. LED retrofits also produce less heat, which reduces cooling costs during Utah summers. Osborne Electric can retrofit your existing fixtures or install new LED-rated housings.</p>
        </div>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-details">
        <summary>Can you install outdoor landscape lighting?</summary>
        <div class="faq-details-body">
          <p>Yes. Osborne Electric installs low-voltage landscape lighting, pathway lights, uplighting for trees and architectural features, and security flood lights. All outdoor lighting is installed with weatherproof connections and meets Utah electrical code requirements for exterior installations.</p>
        </div>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-details">
        <summary>Do I need an electrician to install a chandelier?</summary>
        <div class="faq-details-body">
          <p>A licensed electrician should install any chandelier, especially heavy fixtures that require reinforced junction boxes or new wiring. Improper installation can create fire hazards or cause the fixture to fall. Osborne Electric ensures the electrical box, wiring, and mounting hardware are rated for your fixture's weight and electrical load.</p>
        </div>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-details">
        <summary>What is smart lighting and how does it work?</summary>
        <div class="faq-details-body">
          <p>Smart lighting systems allow you to control lights from your phone, set schedules, adjust brightness, and integrate with voice assistants like Alexa or Google Home. Osborne Electric installs smart switches, dimmers, and whole-home lighting control systems that work with your existing wiring and Wi-Fi network.</p>
        </div>
      </details>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

